content:
Analyze Your Data

Group Your Report Data in Salesforce Classic

Group data in columns or rows in summary, matrix, and joined reports to display meaningful information. For example, group opportunities by Close Date to see closed opportunities or group cases by product to see the number of cases for each product.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)

To create, edit, and delete reports: Enhanced Folder Sharing, Create and Customize Reports, and Report Builder

The Fields pane displays fields from the selected report type, organized by folder. Before you group data in a summary report, drag at least a few fields into the preview pane.

Add a group by dropping a field onto a drop zone. You can also click a column menu for a field in the report and choose Group by this Field.

To remove a group, click the group menu and choose Remove Group or grab the group and drag it back to the Fields pane.

You can also grab the group and drag it to the column bar to remove the group, but keep the field as a column in the report. To change the order of groups, drag the group or click the group menu and choose Move Group Up, Move Group Down for column groupings.

To group data by date fields, select Group Dates By and specify the grouping time frame: day, week, month, quarter, year, and so forth.

In matrix reports, you can have two row and two column groupings. For joined reports, you can use the fields from the Common Fields category in the Fields pane to group across all report blocks.

You can also click Show | Drop Zones to make them visible. 

Grouping Levels
Summary and joined reports can have up to three grouping levels.
Matrix reports can have two row and two column groupings.
title: Grouping Data in Reports
